READY TO BUILD CLEAR BLOCK NEAR WATER!!

Close to bus stop, within minutes to 24 hour boat ramp, local shops including chemist, doctor, ambulance depot, cafes and wineries, primary school and kindergarten. Major shopping centre and Phillip Island approx..
25 mins and easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway.

Description:
CHARMING HOME BY THE BAY
This very affordable home comes with heaps of extras and is located within a short walk to the foreshore and v/line bus services at Pioneer Bay, only 30 minutes to Cranbourne. The home is set on a good sized corner block and would be perfect to subdivide (stca). Ideal to be a bit self sufficient, there are 16 Solar Panels plus space for vegies, fruit trees etc. You will discover a neat and tidy hardy-plank home with open plan living, country style kitchen and a large split system reverse cycle air conditioner. There are two spacious bedrooms, one leading to the extra large rear deck which overlooks the back yard. Outside is a fully fenced yard, garage and carport plus a storage shed. A great opportunity awaits you.

Description:
PARADISE FOUND WITH DIRECT BEACH ACCESS
AUCTION 18TH MARCH 2017 11AM UNLESS SOLD PRIOR
Offered for the first time in 27 years this spectacular property on approximately 8 acres is available to a lucky purchaser.
Absolutely private the long entrance leads to a circular driveway and a very charming mud brick home surrounded by greenery and wildlife equivalent to a private sanctuary.
The three bedroom home boasts plenty of character featuring large windows, timber structures, high ceilings, an open fireplace and a loving feel throughout.
A hidden, unique surprise is an original Melbourne train parked at the property and would be the most exciting project. Boasting so many original features the train could be restored to its former glory and perhaps become guest accommodation or pursue multiple needs that would satisfy your imagination
It is hard to say what is the strongest highlight of this property but some would agree that the walking track with direct beach access to Westernport Bay is extremely rare and highly sought after.
Further improvements include shedding, an abundance of fruit trees and a healthy veggie patch.
Welcome to inspect 1250 Bass Highway, Grantville, your own paradise within 45 min of Melbourneâ??s Eastern suburbs.

Description:
Lifestyle 47 acres, 3 bedroom home with sea views, pizza hut, shedding plus ...
This beautifully secluded 47 acres (19 ha) is approx half pasture & half open mature gums. The residence & pizza hut has been built to capitalise on the great views of Western Port Bay & French Island. Home comprises 3 bedrooms (large main bedroom with generous ensuite with WI shower & his and hers vanity), open plan living room, kitchen featuring timber island bench, dishwasher & pantry, double sliding doors to verandah & pool, 9.5m x 6m rumpus room with doors to pool, split system & wood heater, office, family bathroom with bath & shower plus separate toilet, verandah on 3 sides. 13m x 4m inground solar heated salt swimming pool. Wonderful entertainment building with wood fired pizza oven, kitchen, powder room & verandah opening out to a glorious vista - the way to entertain in style!!
Other features:- 22.8 x 9.1 4/5 fully enclosed high clearance shed with concrete floor, power plus commercial solar panel supply of 20 panels.
Self contained one bedroom shack, double stables plus tack room & menage.
A very peaceful retreat property with total privacy & very well sheltered. Stunning sea views with French & Phillip Islands in the distance. Approx 1 hour from Pakenham. Live the good life!!

Description:
4 Bedroom Family Home - Under Construction Now!
Ideally located in "The Grantville Rise Estate" - surrounded by all new homes, walking tracks, minutes walk to the foreshore & enjoy the great coffee & service that Grantville shops have to offer, as well as having easy access to public V-line transport. Close to all the boat ramps to enjoy the day out fishing on Western Port Bay! Under construction now, this house & land package includes Dishwasher, electric stainless steel hot cooking appliances hotplates & underbench oven, aluminium windows, holland blinds, flyscreens, TV antenna, full ensuite, Brivas split system airconditioning, tiles to the wet areas, quality carpets, grass turf to front yard, topsoil and seed to rear yard. Garage has a remote panel lift door. Fold down clothes line. This home is a turn key package, just move in enjoy & relax with the family! Approximately 1 hour 25 min to Melbourne and 20 mins to Phillip Island, Grantville Rise will be an easy escape from the city, and offers direct access via the Bass Hwy. For further details about this home and land package please click "email agent" link above.

Description:
AS NEW HOME ON MASSIVE BLOCK
Located in a quiet part of Pioneer Bay on approx. 726 m2 is this 3 bedroom 1 year old brick veneer home with garage and large patio area at the rear. The home features an open plan living zone with floating floors throughout. The kitchen has an attached butler's pantry catering for fridge, microwave and all your pantry items. A sliding door leads to a full width undercover outdoor entertaining area with coloured concrete base giving great protection from the elements and extends the open plan living area to the outdoors. Brand new carpet has been installed to the 3 bedrooms where a walk through bathroom services the main bedroom. This compact as new home is perfect for couples, small families or retired couples who seek a low maintenance home with the bonus of a larger than average block. Good quality fencing has been installed with a separate area for pets and a massive open area for extra vehicle parking or plant a vegie garden.

Description:
Quiet Seclusion with Panoramic Views, Horse Lovers Haven
This superb life-style property offers 6 acres of sheltered, useable land & has a substantial and well-designed family home with expansive rural views across the hinterland of Bass.
This colonial style home offers 4 generous sized bedrooms all with built in wardrobes, master bedroom with walk in wardrobe and ensuite. Large open hardwood kitchen with island bench, gas cook top, wall oven, & two door dishwasher leading to the lounge with open views of Western Port Bay and Phillip Island.
Located less than a 10 minute drive to beautiful beaches and within minutes of the Bass Township, this property is ideally situated for an easy commute to Cranbourne or Berwick & into Melbourne.
Features:
* six acres of level land, fully fenced including 5 paddocks with electric fencing
* huge (16m x 12m) barn with 4 Olympic inspired stables, tack room, feed room
* 3 more stables at the rear of the barn leading out to 7 paddocks, self-watering, 4 with lined loose boxes
* sand arena (30 x 45m)
* tank water
* inground salt water pool, solar heated & fenced
* large decked entertainment area
* split system plus ceiling fans
* double garage with remote door
* garden shed (6 x 3m)
Exciting opportunity to secure this highly sought and seldom found 6 acres in a stunning rural setting with great potential to explore many hobby farming or commercial pursuits.
This lifestyle property offers the astute buyer something truly special.

Description:
OUTSTANDING HOME AND BAY VIEWS
Own your own piece of paradise with massive bay views from the large entertainers deck. Freshly painted and lovely landscaped gardens, a newly built car port designed to cater to the biggest of trailer boats, off street parking at front for 2 vehicles and another 4 in the resurfaced driveway make this an brilliant opportunity to secure this delightful and immaculate home situated in the heart of The Gurdies with a rural feel and wineries nearby, you can truly relax here and call it home. Featuring a brand new colour bond roof, a great timber kitchen with servery and 900 ml stainless steel gas stove.
Modern bright bathroom. The living area is spacious with a wood heater, air conditioning, ceiling fan, new Venetian blinds fitted all round and double doors leading to the deck, and what a deck! There are down lights throughout the home, spacious storage under the house, with a third bedroom or studio downstairs. A perfect area to be self sufficient with a large water tank and space for a vegetable patch. A sea change worth a look. Agent available 7 days a week.

Description:
Set on a magnificent 1/4 acre
Set on a magnificent 1/4 acre (approx) or 1016 sqm within walking distance to the foreshore, beach, general store, walking tracks and Community Centre at Corinella, this is the perfect spot to build your new home or holiday house. Close to the highly regarded Bass Coast Primary school and only a stone's throw to Coronet Bay and the many attractions of Phillip Island, you can also explore the stunning ocean views at Kilcunda and enjoy village life at Inverloch. With the many amenities of Wonthaggi only 30 min away, you'll never have to travel far again. This the lowest priced land per sqm in Corinella and offers the best value for discerning buyers only.
